[[File:Rusty sword detail.png|left|70px]]
A '''rusted swords''' is a broken sword that can be repaired by bringing it to [[Tindel Marchant]] in [[Port Khazard]] and paying 100 [[coins]] or repaired on a [[whetstone]] or on an [[armour stand]] in a [[player-owned house]] [[workshop]]. All three options have a chance to break the sword, however the chance of it breaking on the whetstone or armour stand decreases with Smithing level.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/831543833309675521|date=14 February 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.md/hlzmI|archivedate=19 December 2021|quote=Your Smithing level controls the chance of breaking it, but has no bearing on what sword it becomes if you succeed.}} Successfully repairing a rusty sword yields 25 [[Smithing]] [[experience]].

It is obtained as [[Rusty sword#Item sources|loot]] from monsters or by pickpocketing a [[H.A.M. Member]], requiring 15 [[Thieving]].

Giving [[Tindel Marchant]] a rusty sword is an [[Easy Ardougne Diary]] task.

==Possible rewards==
{{Average drop value|Rusty sword|killname=repair}} Getting a rusty sword repaired by [[Tindel Marchant]] yields an average net profit of {{Coins|{{#expr:({{Average drop value|Rusty sword|raw=yes}}-100)round3}}}} [[coins]].

